WEBVTT

00:00.993 --> 00:03.460
<i>Previously on The Secret Life
of the American Teenager</i>

00:03.496 --> 00:05.796
- How are you feeling?
- I'm feeling really happy.

00:06.357 --> 00:08.143
You both look happy.

00:08.144 --> 00:10.391
Oh, we get to find out the sex
of the baby today.

00:10.833 --> 00:12.900
- So it's "we," huh?
- Yep.

00:13.136 --> 00:16.169
I'm ready to have sex with you.
Maybe you should go get tested.

00:16.206 --> 00:18.173
I just need to get some forms
for homeschooling.

00:18.571 --> 00:19.404
Oh, I love homeschooling.

00:20.455 --> 00:22.821
Do you have someone to act
as your teacher at home?

00:22.931 --> 00:25.198
Oh, I don't need a teacher.
I'm gonna do it myself.

00:25.238 --> 00:26.576
I'm sorry. What?

00:26.677 --> 00:28.505
I met him at work,
and we just clicked.

00:28.595 --> 00:30.729
- What is up with you?
- People who meet in high school

00:30.731 --> 00:32.482
don't always stay together.

00:32.484 --> 00:33.097
I got it.

00:33.729 --> 00:36.096
I really hate that you were there for
Amy, but you don't wanna be here for me.

00:36.444 --> 00:37.507
So I wanna go out with him.

00:37.540 --> 00:38.976
You never mentioned
him all summer.

00:39.049 --> 00:40.849
- He was my boss.
- I think 20's a little old.

00:40.920 --> 00:42.952
You're gonna love him. You
just have to give him a chance.

00:42.953 --> 00:45.786
I'm just not gonna get tested.
I don't have anything.

00:46.963 --> 00:48.729
It wouldn't hurt to get tested.

00:51.409 --> 00:53.109
Tell us.
It's a girl.

00:53.178 --> 00:55.878
It's a girl, it's a girl, it's a girl!

00:56.669 --> 00:57.336
Hi, honey. I'm home.

01:02.556 --> 01:04.989
So, that's the deal.
My mom is out of jail.

01:06.500 --> 01:08.400
Hmm. And you're
telling me this because...

01:10.344 --> 01:12.510
Because you granted me
the privilege

01:12.546 --> 01:14.646
of having my son in my home
on weekends,

01:14.647 --> 01:16.747
and I don't wanna lose
the privilege.

01:16.802 --> 01:19.169
I assume I'm not supposed
to be living with an ex-con.

01:19.171 --> 01:21.904
Or an ex-con is not supposed
to be living with me,

01:22.536 --> 01:23.370
even if she is my mother.

01:23.449 --> 01:25.482
So, Ricky, what you're
really looking for,

01:25.487 --> 01:28.754
by telling me that your mom
showed up and is at your apartment,

01:29.787 --> 01:30.520
is not only to protect

01:31.358 --> 01:33.058
your arrangement
with Amy and John,

01:33.093 --> 01:35.160
but you're also looking
for me to tell you

01:35.197 --> 01:37.430
that your mom has to
get out of your apartment,

01:37.597 --> 01:39.997
because you don't want her
to live there anymore.

01:40.008 --> 01:42.108
You want her out
by some order of authority...

01:42.937 --> 01:43.770
that authority being me...

01:43.773 --> 01:47.473
because her living there is not
the best thing for you and your son.

01:47.563 --> 01:48.863
Yeah. Yes, sir.

01:49.565 --> 01:50.398
Let me see what I can do.

01:52.090 --> 01:54.290
Do you know the name
of her parole officer?

01:54.832 --> 01:55.499
Yeah.

01:55.631 --> 01:57.931
I wrote down the information
for you.

01:59.265 --> 02:00.265
Thank you.

02:01.205 --> 02:02.571
All right.
I'll make a call.

02:03.441 --> 02:06.008
But, um, it's just too bad

02:06.742 --> 02:07.609
that we can't find someone

02:08.011 --> 02:09.978
to help turn your mom's
life around.

02:09.979 --> 02:11.810
You know, the same way
that your adopted

02:11.811 --> 02:13.284
parents turned your life around.

02:15.179 --> 02:16.212
Sometimes parents need parents,

02:19.096 --> 02:21.496
and sometimes the child
has to become the parent.

02:23.923 --> 02:26.323
Not me.
I can't do that.

02:31.621 --> 02:33.421
Hang on, hang on.
I'm coming already.

02:35.954 --> 02:36.954
Is Ricky home?

02:38.026 --> 02:40.326
Are you Amy?

02:41.874 --> 02:42.874
Yes, I'm Amy.

02:45.538 --> 02:46.305
Are you Ricky's mother?

02:47.337 --> 02:49.637
- You look just like him.
- You look just like me.

02:51.731 --> 02:54.164
I mean, it's like
looking in a mirror.

02:54.171 --> 02:56.671
I mean, before I was
into alcohol and drugs

02:58.023 --> 02:58.756
and, well, guys and...

02:58.888 --> 03:00.755
Yeah, I was much younger.
Look.

03:02.289 --> 03:02.755
Huh? I mean...

03:02.756 --> 03:05.190
Wow, this is really
kind of sick.

03:06.696 --> 03:07.829
My son is dating his mother.

03:09.230 --> 03:10.530
Not dating. Worse.

03:10.834 --> 03:11.834
Come in.

03:12.336 --> 03:13.269
Please.

03:15.070 --> 03:15.870
Um...

03:16.344 --> 03:18.044
I... I didn't know
that you were...

03:18.210 --> 03:20.043
Oh. Out of jail?
"Yah."

03:20.814 --> 03:23.581
Yeah, I got out yesterday
and showed up last night.

03:25.519 --> 03:27.686
Wow, my good son
is in love with a girl

03:27.687 --> 03:29.381
who looks like
his mother at 17.

03:29.382 --> 03:31.216
I can't get over it.

03:32.621 --> 03:34.054
Yeah.
Come on. Sit down.

03:35.125 --> 03:36.758
I... I can't.
I have to get to school.

03:36.759 --> 03:39.700
I dropped John off at the nursery
a little early this morning.

03:39.701 --> 03:41.868
Thought I'd surprise Ricky
and drop by.

03:43.533 --> 03:44.366
Oh, he... he left already.

03:44.367 --> 03:47.404
What, you thought you'd surprise
him, or you thought you'd catch him?

03:48.573 --> 03:49.240
I think I better go.

03:50.044 --> 03:51.878
Oh, no, no.
I wish you'd stay.

03:53.313 --> 03:54.146
I really wish you'd stay.

03:55.150 --> 03:57.350
I've been dying to meet you.
Just dying to meet you.

03:57.414 --> 03:59.781
Of course, I wasn't
expecting me, but...

04:00.855 --> 04:02.422
I really have to go.

04:04.322 --> 04:05.122
Okay. If you have to go.

04:05.726 --> 04:07.626
I guess school's
important, too.

04:08.993 --> 04:09.993
Yeah, school's very important.

04:11.298 --> 04:12.098
It was nice meeting you.

04:13.433 --> 04:14.133
Nora. My name's Nora.

04:14.134 --> 04:15.968
You know what?
Before you go,

04:17.470 --> 04:18.170
could I just ask you,

04:19.505 --> 04:20.406
do you mind if I meet John?

04:21.607 --> 04:22.440
I really wanna meet John.

04:23.778 --> 04:26.745
Uh, if Ricky says it's okay,
then, yeah, of course it's okay.

04:27.744 --> 04:28.678
I mean, John's his son, too.

04:29.778 --> 04:30.578
Great.

04:31.151 --> 04:33.251
So, if I get my
18-year-old son's permission,

04:33.252 --> 04:34.918
then I get to meet my grandson?

04:35.721 --> 04:37.921
Yeah, I think it has to be
his decision.

04:38.558 --> 04:39.358
I don't really know you.

04:40.562 --> 04:42.662
Then you should get to know me.

04:44.265 --> 04:46.299
Come on. Please stay.
Please?

04:48.130 --> 04:50.196
I will tell you Ricky stories.

04:50.203 --> 04:53.336
Come on. What are they gonna
teach you at school today

04:53.377 --> 04:55.344
that's better
than Ricky stories?

04:57.380 --> 04:58.680
<i>Falling in love</i>

05:00.666 --> 05:02.300
<i>Is such an easy thing to do</i>

05:03.575 --> 05:05.241
<i>Birds can do it We can do it</i>

05:06.741 --> 05:07.718
<i>Let's stop talking</i>

05:07.719 --> 05:08.641
<i>Let's get to it</i>

05:09.323 --> 05:09.923
<i>Let's fall in love</i>

05:15.223 --> 05:17.157
- It won't last.
- It might.

05:17.158 --> 05:17.712
It won't.

05:17.713 --> 05:19.927
You know, I've done
some research,

05:19.928 --> 05:21.546
<i>and as it turns
out, some teenagers</i>

05:21.547 --> 05:23.298
actually do better with
homeschooling.

05:23.568 --> 05:25.634
Ashley might thrive
in homeschooling.

05:25.635 --> 05:27.154
You're just gonna have
to let her see how

05:27.155 --> 05:28.672
she likes it and see
if it works for her.

05:28.673 --> 05:29.968
It's not gonna work for
her, and she's not

05:29.969 --> 05:31.172
even gonna try to
make it work for her.

05:31.210 --> 05:33.677
She's only doing this
because you told her she could.

05:34.409 --> 05:35.375
Well, you told her she could.

05:35.614 --> 05:37.481
Only because you
told her she could.

05:38.446 --> 05:39.480
Well, she wants to do it, so...

05:39.878 --> 05:42.112
So, the question is,
why does she wanna do it?

05:43.285 --> 05:44.818
I don't think there is a "why."

05:44.890 --> 05:46.690
She wants to
'cause she wants to.

05:46.691 --> 05:48.924
It's something different to do,
and teenagers like being different.

05:48.960 --> 05:51.060
I don't like teenagers
being different.

05:51.411 --> 05:53.479
I want her to be the same as
everyone else and go to school.

05:53.531 --> 05:55.531
Well, you're gonna
have to tell her that then.

05:55.616 --> 05:56.349
I can't tell her that.

05:57.079 --> 05:58.712
I used to be the good cop
to your bad cop,

05:58.774 --> 06:00.474
and now you've decided
to be the good cop, too.

06:00.678 --> 06:02.345
<i>She has no discipline
in her life.</i>

06:02.423 --> 06:03.682
One of us has to say no
to her, and it can't

06:03.683 --> 06:04.913
be me, because I'm the
one living with her.

06:04.960 --> 06:07.327
No, it has to be you, because
you're the one living with her.

06:07.826 --> 06:09.795
<i>Besides, you're the one who
thinks that she shouldn't do it.</i>

06:09.961 --> 06:12.327
So you tell her no.
I think it could work.

06:12.566 --> 06:16.536
It can't work. She has no discipline,
no motivation, and no mommy.

06:18.002 --> 06:18.969
This is broken homeschooling.

06:19.138 --> 06:20.971
Living with
two teenage daughters

06:21.806 --> 06:23.772
isn't as easy
as you thought it would be?

06:25.243 --> 06:27.176
Lauren, you have to
go to school.

06:27.177 --> 06:29.880
I can't. I can't go to
school. I don't wanna see him.

06:29.881 --> 06:32.448
Well, maybe if you see him,
he'll change his mind.

06:32.785 --> 06:34.519
I don't care
if he changes his mind

06:34.556 --> 06:36.556
after he's already
broken my heart.

06:37.133 --> 06:40.057
And what difference does it
make if he changes his mind?

06:40.058 --> 06:41.904
I'll never feel the
same about him.

06:42.305 --> 06:43.205
Well, what do you wanna do?

06:44.475 --> 06:46.675
I just want to stay in bed.
I'm sick.

06:46.840 --> 06:49.206
No, you aren't. Not really.
Not sick sick.

06:49.352 --> 06:53.489
I know. I'm worse than sick.
I'm practically dead.

06:54.131 --> 06:55.098
Well, I have to go to school.

06:55.153 --> 06:57.120
I hate to leave you here dead,
but I have to go to school.

06:58.762 --> 07:00.396
Why? Why can't you stay with me?

07:00.699 --> 07:02.999
Our parents are working.
They won't know.

07:04.128 --> 07:05.028
I don't wanna be by myself.

07:05.029 --> 07:08.233
Well, yeah, but, you know,
we just got off restriction,

07:09.271 --> 07:09.704
and I just...

07:09.705 --> 07:11.875
I feel like we should go.
I mean, we should go.

07:13.877 --> 07:14.877
Oh. I know what this is about.

07:15.678 --> 07:16.411
This is about Stanley.

07:17.646 --> 07:18.313
Well, yeah, kind of.

07:18.316 --> 07:20.249
I mean, he's supposed
to meet my dad tonight.

07:22.585 --> 07:26.154
Then just go without me then.
Just go without me.

07:27.286 --> 07:28.053
I'm not going. I can't.

07:29.691 --> 07:30.991
Okay. I'll ask.

07:31.423 --> 07:32.190
If I don't ask, then...

07:35.129 --> 07:36.729
Madison?

07:37.100 --> 07:38.534
Hey, Dad.

07:38.802 --> 07:39.735
I need to ask you something.

07:40.803 --> 07:41.236
Okay. Ask me.

07:41.267 --> 07:43.300
But if you wanna ask me
if you can date Jack again,

07:44.171 --> 07:45.738
I told you,
you can date Jack again.

07:46.044 --> 07:48.043
Oh, no. I want you
to meet Stanley tonight.

07:48.044 --> 07:50.978
Stanley's coming over tonight.
You didn't forget, did you?

07:51.911 --> 07:52.578
No, I didn't forget.

07:54.483 --> 07:56.653
Well, uh, Lauren isn't
gonna go to school today

07:56.654 --> 07:59.187
'cause Jesse broke up with her,
and she's really upset.

07:59.188 --> 08:01.489
- So can I stay with her?
- And miss school? No.

08:01.490 --> 08:03.115
Madison, you have to
go to school, and you

08:03.116 --> 08:04.627
should get Lauren to
go to school, too.

08:05.327 --> 08:06.260
<i>I mean, these things happen.</i>

08:06.295 --> 08:08.364
Teenagers break up,
they get back together,

08:08.365 --> 08:10.432
they break up again,
they get back together again.

08:10.433 --> 08:12.733
This doesn't mean that
it's over for her and Jesse.

08:13.003 --> 08:15.170
This doesn't even mean
that it's over for you and Jack.

08:15.205 --> 08:17.405
Oh, no, things are over
for me and Jack.

08:18.838 --> 08:19.838
Go to school.

08:22.748 --> 08:25.115
I don't think Jesse
meant to break up with Lauren.

08:25.558 --> 08:28.291
- I think it just happened.
- That's between the two of them.

08:29.659 --> 08:31.559
This is between the...
three of us.

08:31.560 --> 08:34.496
I really think that this is
an opportunity for you, Jack.

08:34.498 --> 08:36.198
Lauren is gonna be
at home today.

08:36.198 --> 08:38.635
Madison is gonna be without
her best friend at school.

08:38.673 --> 08:41.173
This is your opportunity
to get back in the game, son.

08:42.504 --> 08:43.504
And when you back in the game,

08:44.241 --> 08:46.209
just remember what
the rules of the game are.

08:47.579 --> 08:48.579
Yes, sir.

08:48.748 --> 08:51.248
But is there any kind
of compromising on that?

08:52.017 --> 08:53.717
No. Got it.

08:53.859 --> 08:55.159
Have a nice day.

09:02.091 --> 09:03.991
Where are you?

09:03.992 --> 09:07.096
Oh, I just finished my
conversation with Madison's dad.

09:07.995 --> 09:09.028
Hey, is Grace dropping you off?

09:09.029 --> 09:10.664
I texted Grace to drop you off.

09:10.067 --> 09:12.034
If I drop you off,
you'll be late.

09:12.498 --> 09:14.764
I'm vice president.
I can't be late.

09:15.236 --> 09:17.036
I know, Tom.
Do you want me to call Grace?

09:18.674 --> 09:19.041
I call her.

09:19.109 --> 09:21.475
She's not going to do
anything for you.

09:22.742 --> 09:23.742
She hates you!

09:29.219 --> 09:31.152
Hello?

09:32.524 --> 09:34.857
Hello. Why are you talking
on your phone?

09:35.591 --> 09:38.424
Because you were calling me
just as I was walking in.

09:38.892 --> 09:39.392
It's not funny.

09:39.630 --> 09:41.330
Yes, it is.
It's hysterical.

09:41.531 --> 09:43.897
If you're in a good mood,
it's hysterical.

09:43.898 --> 09:45.931
I, myself, am not
in a good mood,

09:46.269 --> 09:48.235
otherwise I'd
be laughing hysterically.

09:49.139 --> 09:49.872
I need a ride to work.

09:50.371 --> 09:52.704
I know. Jack texted me.
I'll take you.

09:54.641 --> 09:55.441
Thanks.

09:56.879 --> 09:59.012
So where is Mr. Irresponsible?
Why can't he take you?

10:00.466 --> 10:00.899
I never tell.

10:00.998 --> 10:03.931
I don't really care. I just need
to tell Adrian what I'm doing.

10:04.295 --> 10:05.295
Make it quick.

10:11.346 --> 10:12.179
Hey, are you on your way?

10:12.079 --> 10:13.415
Yeah. I need to drop Tom off.
Do you wanna come?

10:13.716 --> 10:16.049
No. We're gonna be late
if we drop Tom off.

10:16.050 --> 10:17.180
You know, you're right.

10:17.181 --> 10:19.586
Maybe we should just
forget about it for today.

10:20.254 --> 10:21.887
- You wanna ditch?
- No. Do you?

10:22.519 --> 10:23.519
Yeah, I do.

10:23.788 --> 10:24.455
School just started.

10:25.326 --> 10:26.059
We can't ditch school.

10:26.393 --> 10:28.527
We could. And, you know,
school just started,

10:28.528 --> 10:30.895
so there's probably
not that much stuff going on.

10:30.896 --> 10:33.232
- What is wrong with you?
- Nothing.

10:34.237 --> 10:36.904
Oh, just go get the test,
if that's what Grant wants.

10:37.205 --> 10:39.838
No. And I'm not showing
my face at that school.

10:41.074 --> 10:42.374
Oh, Grace, come on.

10:42.576 --> 10:43.876
No, you come on.

10:44.041 --> 10:44.908
I'll get a ride to school.

10:45.458 --> 10:46.191
- Let's go!

10:52.640 --> 10:54.340
- Are you okay?
- I'm fine.

10:54.924 --> 10:56.757
- Where are you?
- Still here.

10:56.758 --> 10:59.961
- Grace was going to pick me up.
- "Was"?

11:00.530 --> 11:03.496
Would you stop worrying, please?
I'm fine. I'll be there.

11:03.497 --> 11:05.700
- I'll come back and get you.
- Don't be ridiculous.

11:05.701 --> 11:08.301
Well, then, I'll get Mike,
our driver, to drive you.

11:08.970 --> 11:09.870
I can drive me.

11:11.016 --> 11:13.616
Why was Grace gonna drive you
in the first place?

11:14.155 --> 11:15.290
I don't know.

11:15.291 --> 11:17.555
I think she had some plan
to ditch school.

11:17.556 --> 11:19.956
- She doesn't wanna see Grant.
- Why?

11:20.327 --> 11:22.327
Well, it's just
something stupid... sexing.

11:22.731 --> 11:25.331
Did you think about what
I asked you about last night?

11:26.136 --> 11:28.336
Ben, I'm not gonna
live with you, okay?

11:28.337 --> 11:30.325
I don't wanna live with you.
We're friends.

11:30.326 --> 11:31.636
Friends don't live together.

11:32.472 --> 11:34.872
Friends having babies
with friends live together.

11:36.144 --> 11:37.144
Or they could.

11:37.975 --> 11:38.642
I'll think about it.

11:40.169 --> 11:41.469
Have you seen Amy?

11:42.032 --> 11:42.732
No longer my concern.

11:44.604 --> 11:44.737
Hey.

11:44.738 --> 11:47.111
Hey, did you know Grace
is ditching school?

11:47.112 --> 11:48.405
What is wrong with her?

11:48.939 --> 11:51.074
She was supposed to pick up Adrian,
who's now gonna be late for school.

11:51.679 --> 11:53.347
Why would Grace ditch school?

11:53.348 --> 11:56.148
She didn't say anything to me
about ditching school.

11:55.644 --> 11:58.077
Of course, she's not
really talking to me.

11:58.685 --> 12:00.085
Um, something to do with sex?

12:00.086 --> 12:02.687
Oh, I'm out on that. I have
nothing more to say on that.

12:02.688 --> 12:04.754
Grace is no longer my concern.

12:06.739 --> 12:07.739
Where are you?

12:08.374 --> 12:10.141
I stopped by
to see you this morning.

12:10.309 --> 12:12.009
I thought maybe
I could be with you

12:12.345 --> 12:13.945
when you got
your test results back.

12:13.583 --> 12:15.583
I thought maybe
they would call this morning.

12:15.320 --> 12:17.487
You're at my apartment
with my mother?

12:18.688 --> 12:19.488
Test results? What test?

12:20.290 --> 12:21.124
Ricky had a test already?

12:21.125 --> 12:24.625
It's the second day of school.

